# Phase 42: Upload Flow Perfection & UI Centering

## Problem Statement
The Upload page is currently "left-heavy," with fields and boxes aligned to the left rather than centered. Additionally, users report a "Network error during upload," which needs robust debugging and a fix.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - I will be narrowing the layout of the Upload page to center the content more effectively on desktop.
> - I will add more granular error reporting to the upload process to catch exactly where the "Network error" occurs.

## Proposed Changes

### [UI] Upload Page Overhaul
#### [MODIFY] [app/upload/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx)
- Wrap the main content in a more constrained container to center it.
- Change the layout from `lg:grid-cols-5` to a more balanced structure (e.g., single column or centered two-column).
- Center the header and upload zones.

### [Fix] Robust Upload Debugging
#### [MODIFY] [app/upload/page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx)
- Update the `XMLHttpRequest` `error` listener to log the `xhr.status` and `xhr.response`.
- Double-check pre-signed URL headers.

